-- EU Sells 4 Million Carbon Permits for 2013 at 7.30 Euros on EEX
-- B y   A l e s s a n d r o   V i t e l l i
-- 2012-11-15T14:21:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-11-15/eu-sells-4-million-carbon-permits-for-2013-at-7-30-euros-on-eex.html
The European Union sold more than 4
million EU spot carbon permits for the third phase of the
region’s carbon market, which starts in 2013, at 7.30 euros a
metric ton in an auction on the European Energy Exchange AG.  The sale ended at 3 p.m. Berlin time. EU spot permits for
the second phase of the bloc’s market, which ends in 2012, were
bid at 7.33 euros and offered at 7.43 euros a ton at the same
time on Caisse des Depots et des Consignations and  NYSE
Euronext’s (NYX)  Paris-based Bluenext SA exchange.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alessandro Vitelli in London at 
 avitelli1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
